transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Viagra, I can help you today.

Speaker 2: Yes, I'm calling because I want to cancel a prescription.

Speaker 1: I can take a look into your account.

Speaker 2: What's your zip code?

Speaker 1: It's 78218.

Speaker 2: And your last name?

Speaker 1: Luis, R-U-I-Z.

Speaker 2: R-U-I-Z.

Speaker 1: First name?

Speaker 2: Edward.

Speaker 1: Okay, one second.

Speaker 2: Okay, so I do see you're currently a member for the Viagra AGV,

Speaker 1: one of our best-selling Viagras that we offer through Pfizer.

Speaker 2: The moment we do cancel out your order, sir, keep in mind,

Speaker 1: the doctor will eliminate the prescription

Speaker 2: and you wouldn't be able to order this in the future.

Speaker 1: However, what I could always do for you is just freeze out the account.

Speaker 2: That way, whenever you want to order them down the road,

Speaker 1: you still have access to them.

Speaker 2: Did you want to make that change to your account?

Speaker 1: Yeah, just freeze it up until I – because I have, like, four bottles right now.

Speaker 2: Oh, yeah, no, not a problem at all.

Speaker 1: Our prescriptions, we just freeze them out for half the year, so just give us a call.

Speaker 2: If you need to freeze it further than that

Speaker 1: or if you need more time to get it sooner, because we can always send it sooner too.

Speaker 2: But you're also on that part.

Speaker 1: I changed you over to Applied.

Speaker 2: Okay, that's fine.

Speaker 1: All right, you have a good rest of your day, sir.

Speaker 2: And if anything comes up, let us know.

Speaker 1: All right, thank you.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
